---
title: Herb-Grilled Steak & Old Bay Shrimp with Caesar Salad & Garlic Bread
description: Back in the day, surf ’n’ turf was just a fancy restaurant thing. Now? It’s a cold-can-in-hand, grill-by-the-pool, invite-your-friends type of thing. You’ll make a classic Caesar salad and a flavored butter in the kitchen, then head outside to grill herby bavette steak and spicy Old Bay shrimp tossed with parsley and lemon. Grilling lends smoky char lines to garlic bread too, then everything’s piled high for a five-star meal with a backyard feel. Long live summer!
